                <h1>"Don't Tread on Me: A Symbol of American Freedom"</h1>
                <p>"Don't Tread on Me" is a historic motto associated with American independence and resilience. Originating from the Gadsden flag, it symbolizes a call for liberty and warning against oppression. The phrase embodies a spirit of defiance, urging others to respect individual freedom and personal rights recognized throughout American history.</p>
